article.description: — Jao Ituka had 22 points as Marist narrowly beat Canisius 71-70 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Ituka scores 22 to lead Marist past Canisius 71-70
article.linkText: Ituka scores 22 to lead Marist past Canisius 71-70
article.story: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. -- — Jao Ituka had 22 points as Marist narrowly beat Canisius 71-70 on Saturday night. Noah Harris had 14 points for Marist (10-13, 5-9 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Ricardo Wright added 13 points. Jordan Henderson had 19 points for the Golden Griffins (8-17, 4-10). Ahamadou Fofana added 16 points. Armon Harried, the Golden Griffins' leading scorer heading into the matchup at 12 points per game, scored 4 points on 2-of-11 shooting. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
